<h3>What Caused the Evening Drop?</h3>

<p>Several factors appear to be driving the evening sell-off:</p>

<ol>
    <li><strong>Profit-taking from the morning rally</strong> ” BONK's +15% and DOGE's +12.4% were unsustainable. Traders who bought in May took profits into strength.</li>
    <li><strong>BTC weakness leading the market</strong> ” When Bitcoin drops 4.5%, all altcoins follow. Meme coins, being the most volatile sector, get hit hardest percentage-wise.</li>
    <li><strong>Evening session low liquidity</strong> ” As US trading winds down and Asia hasn't fully ramped up, liquidity thins. Thin liquidity = amplified moves in both directions.</li>
    <li><strong>Technical breakdown at $70K</strong> ” BTC lost the $70K round number, which triggered stop-loss cascades from leveraged longs.</li>
</ol>

<div class="warning-box">
    <strong>⚠ Important Context:</strong><br>
    A 4.5% BTC drop in a single evening session is notable but not alarming. Since the start of 2026, we've seen 8 similar pullbacks ” and BTC recovered above its previous level within 3-7 days in 6 of those 8 cases. This looks like a normal correction within an uptrend, not a trend reversal.
</div>

<h2>Overnight Trading Strategy: How to Position for the Asian Session</h2>

<p>With US markets closing and Asian markets about to take over, the overnight session (June 2-3) has its own rules. Here's how to position:</p>

<h3>1. Don't Chase the Drop ” Let Support Prove Itself</h3>
<p>The worst thing you can do in an evening sell-off is panic-sell at the bottom of the move, or FOMO-buy the first green candle. Let BTC establish a base at $68K or test $66.5K first. If BTC holds $68K through the Asian night (0:00-6:00 UTC), that's a bullish signal for Wednesday.</p>

<h3>2. Watch $DKING for the First Recovery Signal</h3>
<p>Based on today's relative strength pattern, <strong>$DKING is the most likely meme coin to lead the recovery</strong> if BTC stabilizes. During today's morning rally, $DKING underperformed (+8.2% vs BONK's +15.1%), meaning it has <em>less profit-taking pressure</em> on the way down. When the bounce comes, capital tends to rotate into the relative-strength leader.</p>

<h3>3. Set Alerts, Not Orders</h3>
<p>Don't place market orders during thin-liquidity overnight hours. Instead, set price alerts at:</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>BTC reclaims $69,500</strong> ” First sign of recovery strength</li>
    <li><strong>BTC breaks $66,500</strong> ” Warning signal, consider reducing positions</li>
    <li><strong>$DKING holds above current level for 4+ hours</strong> ” Confirmation of relative strength</li>
</ul>

<h3>4. Position Sizing for Overnight Risk</h3>
<p>Overnight sessions carry higher gap risk. Consider reducing leverage or position size by 30-50% overnight until BTC establishes a clear direction.</p>

